WEBVTT

00:00.800 --> 00:02.260
<i>Previously on “Boston Legal”…</i>

00:02.300 --> 00:04.360
Jerry, you've made rather
a point of saying

00:04.400 --> 00:06.860
that this is the year
that you will make partner.

00:06.900 --> 00:09.460
There are many ways of
getting that job done, Jerry.

00:09.500 --> 00:13.000
Prancing around the office
as little Bo Peep

00:13.000 --> 00:14.860
is not one of the better ones.

00:14.900 --> 00:17.060
Do you know what happens to
lawyers who make partner, Jerry?

00:17.100 --> 00:19.500
They become locked-in… lifers.

00:19.500 --> 00:21.460
I'm not sure
that's something you want.

00:21.500 --> 00:23.060
Take off your pants, Denise.

00:23.100 --> 00:28.000
See, you like to talk.
I don't. I like to do.

00:28.000 --> 00:29.900
Surely you jest.

00:34.400 --> 00:36.644
My God, Denny.
Can you believe it?

00:36.900 --> 00:38.946
Election day
is almost upon us.

00:39.300 --> 00:42.460
–You gonna vote?
–Of course I'm gonna vote. Are you?

00:42.500 --> 00:44.360
Never missed
a presidential election.

00:44.400 --> 00:45.660
And I'm usually right, too.

00:45.700 --> 00:49.260
I've been on the winning side
8 times out of the last 11.

00:49.300 --> 00:51.016
–That's impressive.
–Yeah.

00:51.200 --> 00:52.960
Also an uncanny coincidence,

00:53.000 --> 00:56.498
since 8 out of the last 11
have also gone republican.

00:56.700 --> 00:57.800
Do tell.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.060
So you just <i>always</i>
vote republican?

01:00.100 --> 01:02.800
–I vote my values.
–So this week—

01:02.800 --> 01:04.860
I thought we weren't
gonna go there.

01:04.900 --> 01:06.682
You're right.
You're right.

01:08.400 --> 01:09.360
Who are you voting—
–Alan.

01:09.400 --> 01:12.060
Never mind. I'm not
looking to discuss it.

01:12.100 --> 01:15.000
I just… Who?

01:16.000 --> 01:17.100
McCain.

01:18.100 --> 01:19.100
Seriously?

01:19.100 --> 01:20.420
I'm serious. McCain.

01:21.000 --> 01:21.800
Ah.

01:24.300 --> 01:25.400
–Denny—
–Alan.

01:25.400 --> 01:26.984
You're right.
I'm sorry.

01:27.900 --> 01:28.760
–It's just…
–Come on.

01:28.800 --> 01:30.660
–…what would possibly possess—
–Hey.

01:30.700 --> 01:31.960
I'm sorry. Forget it.

01:32.000 --> 01:36.200
The important thing
is that we both vote.

01:36.500 --> 01:38.160
–That's right.
–To voting.

01:38.200 --> 01:39.300
Hear, hear.

01:43.600 --> 01:45.460
–It's just—
–Okay, that's it.

01:45.500 --> 01:48.160
No, no, no, no, no, no.
All right, how about this?

01:48.200 --> 01:50.900
I give you my word,
I will not speak.

01:50.900 --> 01:53.460
I will not open my mouth
if you'll just give me

01:53.500 --> 01:57.400
two reasons why you're voting
for John McCain—just two.

01:57.400 --> 01:58.460
That's a discussion.

01:58.500 --> 01:59.600
No, it's not.

02:00.000 --> 02:03.036
One person talking
does not a discussion make.

02:03.400 --> 02:06.000
Just two reasons.
I won't talk.

02:07.700 --> 02:08.600
Promise.

02:10.300 --> 02:11.200
Okay.

02:15.200 --> 02:18.038
If McCain wins,
he'll help save the salmon.

02:18.200 --> 02:19.718
–What?
–You're talking.

02:19.800 --> 02:20.500
I…

02:21.400 --> 02:23.660
The wild salmon stocks
in Canada are threatened,

02:23.700 --> 02:27.000
either by climate change,
fish farming, sea lice.

02:27.100 --> 02:30.160
Once the salmon go,
there goes half the ecosystem.

02:30.200 --> 02:31.850
I don't need to tell you.

02:35.100 --> 02:36.760
And, uh, McCain
will save them?

02:36.800 --> 02:38.300
–Not directly…
–Wh—

02:38.300 --> 02:40.660
…but the polls show
that if McCain wins,

02:40.700 --> 02:42.900
it's like a third term
of Bush.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.960
A lot of Americans
will immigrate to Canada,

02:45.000 --> 02:46.100
the smart ones.

02:46.500 --> 02:48.760
The intelligence level
of Canada goes up,

02:48.800 --> 02:51.836
and they'll figure out
how to save the salmon.

02:53.900 --> 02:55.352
And the second reason?

02:55.600 --> 02:56.600
Women…

02:57.300 --> 02:58.200
are easier…

02:59.100 --> 03:01.160
during a republican
administration.

03:01.200 --> 03:02.100
It's a fact.

03:02.100 --> 03:05.300
During democratic regimes,
volunteerism goes up.

03:06.100 --> 03:08.760
And you get a lot of women
running around for this cause or that,

03:08.800 --> 03:11.760
and they start to think that
they have something to say.

03:11.800 --> 03:13.660
Republicans tend
to reinforce the idea

03:13.700 --> 03:17.100
that woman's place
is in the home on her back.

03:17.100 --> 03:19.900
Now I'm not even
taking into account

03:20.200 --> 03:23.060
all the women that'll
be depressed if McCain wins.

03:23.100 --> 03:25.900
Sad girls are easy girls.

03:26.600 --> 03:28.060
I don't need to tell you.

03:28.100 --> 03:29.400
They're vulnerable.

03:29.900 --> 03:32.300
Salmon and women, Alan.

03:33.700 --> 03:35.960
In the end,
it's all about spawning.

03:36.000 --> 03:37.254
Drill, baby, drill.

03:38.600 --> 03:40.100
You vote your values.

